-- U.S. Exporters Report Sales of 107,214 Tons of Wheat to Japan
-- B y   P a t r i c k   M c K i e r n a n
-- 2012-07-16T13:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/u-s-exporters-report-sales-of-107-214-tons-of-wheat-to-japan.html
U.S. exporters reported sales of
107,214 metric tons of wheat to Japan for delivery by May 31,
the  U.S. Department of Agriculture  said today in a statement.  Of the total, 69,784 tons is hard red spring wheat and
37,430 tons is soft white wheat, the agency said.  Shippers must report any export transaction of 100,000 tons
or more for any commodity sold in one day to a single
destination.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick McKiernan in New York at 
 pmckiernan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net  